edu.lehigh.cse.lol

Class Score

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.lehigh.cse.lol.Score

  • public class Score
extends java.lang.Object
    Score is used by Level to track the progress through a level. There are four things tracked: the number of heroes created and destroyed, the number of enemies created and destroyed, the number of heroes at destinations, and the number of (each type of) goodie that has been collected. Apart from storing the counts, this class provides a public interface for manipulating the goodie counts, and a set of internal convenience methods for updating values and checking for win/lose. It also manages the mode of the level (i.e., what must be done to finish the level... collecting goodies, reaching a destination, etc).
